note.body:
I did a quick pass through the changes here, and it looks pretty good. I've left a few inline comments.

I do kind of worry that the code paths trying to distinguish enums from flags are more fragile now, since it might not be immediately obvious that the order of the branches in the if statement are important. I wonder if it would be worth converting code like:

```c
...
} else if (GI_IS_FLAGS_INFO (info)) {
    // foo
} else if (GI_IS_ENUM_INFO (info)) {
    // bar
} else ...
```

to:

```c
...
} else if (GI_IS_ENUM_INFO (info)) {
    if (GI_IS_FLAGS_INFO (info)) {
        // foo
    } else {
        // bar
    }
} else ...
```

The main con is that it is another level of indentation. As a pro, it's one less type check in the non-enum/flags case.
